
[1]stratum

   STRATUM, n. plu. stratums or strata. The latter is most common. [L., to
   spread or lay.]

   1. In geology and mineralogy, a layer; any species of earth, sand, coal
   and the like, arranged in a flat form, distinct from the adjacent
   matter. The thicker strata are called beds; and these beds are
   sometimes stratified.

   2. A bed or layer artificially made.
